author: CNN
description:
Venezuelan Vice President Delcy Rodríguez asserted that Nicolás Maduro is “the only president of Venezuela” after US forces captured Maduro early Saturday.

In a defiant address broadcast from Caracas, Rodríguez said that Venezuelans “must not become slaves again.” “We will never be a colony again,” she said. She also condemned the “aggression” from the United States and declared that the “words of the president are the only ones we are guided by.”

“We demand the immediate release of President Nicolás Maduro and his wife Cilia Flores, the only president of Venezuela, President Nicolás Maduro,” Rodríguez said during a session of the National Defense Council broadcast by state television channel VTV.

Alongside other top officials, Rodríguez said that Venezuela’s territorial integrity was “savagely attacked” by the operation that the US carried out in Caracas and other parts of the country.

title: Venezuela's VP demands 'immediate release' of Maduro and his wife

author: CNN
description:
In a phone interview with Fox News, President Donald Trump provided details on how the capture of Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro unfolded.

While he was talking, CNN also learned from sources that the Trump administration began preparing in mid-December for the secretive operation to strike Venezuela and capture Maduro.

Maduro and his wife are aboard the USS Iwo Jima heading to New York, Trump said adding that he spoke to the Venezuelan president a week ago. Vice President JD Vance also posted on social media, saying Trump offered “multiple off ramps” before the US executed the operation.

Trump said he watched the complex capture of Maduro in real-time from a room in his Mar-a-Lago resort in Florida, alongside military generals.

description:
Venezuelan President Nicolas Maduro has been captured and flown out of Venezuela after the US carried out a large scale strike on the capital city of Caracas, US President Donald Trump announced, adding there will be a news conference today at 11am E.T.

US Attorney General Pam Bondi says Maduro has been indicted in New York on drugs and weapons charges. Earlier, US Secretary of State Marco Rubio told a GOP senator that Maduro will stand trial in the US and that he anticipates no further action.
